## File Naming Patterns to Detect

**If you see these patterns in application directories, they MUST be moved:**

- `*QA*.md` ‚Üí `memory-bank/reports/qa-report-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*TEST*.md` ‚Üí `memory-bank/reports/test-report-[task_id]-*.md` or `documentation/reports/testing-plan-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*DEBUG*.md` ‚Üí `memory-bank/reports/debug-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*DIAGNOSTIC*.md` ‚Üí `memory-bank/reports/diagnostic-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*DEPLOY*.md` ‚Üí `documentation/reports/deploy-check-[task_id]-*.md` or `documentation/deployment/`
- `*TESTING*.md` ‚Üí `documentation/reports/testing-plan-[task_id]-*.md` or `documentation/reports/manual-testing-checklist-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*INTEGRATION*.md` ‚Üí `documentation/reports/integration-test-plan-[task_id]-*.md`
- `*CHECKLIST*.md` ‚Üí `documentation/reports/[task_id]-*.md` or `memory-bank/reports/[task_id]-*.md` (depending on type)
- `*CREATIVE*.md` ‚Üí `memory-bank/creative/creative-[task_id]-*.md`

## Enforcement Actions

**When detecting MD files in prohibited locations:**

1. **Identify file type** (QA report, test plan, debug report, etc.)
2. **Determine correct location** per rules above
3. **Move file** to correct location with proper naming
4. **Update any references** to the file path
5. **Document migration** if needed

